nerating the summary. Must test the full posting-then-summarizing flow to catch when findings are dropped or added inconsistently between the two steps.","test_description":"Test that the complete review workflow posts both inline comments and a summary comment, then verify that every finding listed in the summary comment has a corresponding inline comment posted to the PR. Catch cases where findings appear in the summary but lack inline comments, or vice versa.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration test of the full posting and summarizing pipeline catches mismatches that a Unit test of summary logic alone would miss.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence—reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment—completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"The behavior explicitly requires 'a real pull request', which means real GitHub API interaction (System-level) and real LLM analysis (Agentic-level). Real failures could stem from GitHub API timeouts/failures, LLM API errors, or orchestration breakdowns between the steps. Neither System nor Agentic alone is sufficient; both must work together in coordination. This is a multi-step pipeline requiring real external dependencies and coordination.","test_description":"Test the end-to-end agent workflow: fetch a real pull request from GitHub, have the agent analyze the diff with real LLM calls, post inline code review comments to the PR, post a summary comment, and verify the entire sequence completes without errors or manual intervention. Verify that all comments appear on the PR and the workflow exits cleanly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Workflow test integrates real GitHub API and real LLM steps; either mock step would hide real failures in that dependency.","level_probabilities":